  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can you use Roku to browse the internet?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, as of my last update, Roku devices do not have a built-in web browser. Roku's primary function is to stream digital media, and it offers a variety of streaming services and apps such as Netflix, Hulu, Amazon Prime Video, and more.\n\nIf you want to browse the internet on your Roku device, you would generally need to use a workaround such as screen mirroring from another device.\n\nHere are two methods you can try:\n\n### 1. Screen Mirroring from an Android Device or Windows PC:\nRoku supports screen mirroring for Android devices and Windows PCs. This allows you to display your computer or phone's screens directly on your Roku-enabled TV.\n\n#### Setup for Android:\n1. Make sure your Android device is connected to the same Wi-Fi network as your Roku.\n2. Open the Settings on your Android device.\n3. Navigate to the Display settings.\n4. Look for an option named \"Cast\" or \"Screen Mirroring.\"\n5. Choose your Roku device from the list of available devices.\n6. Once connected, open a web browser on your Android device, and it will be mirrored on your Roku.\n\n#### Setup for Windows:\n1. Ensure your PC is connected to the same Wi-Fi network as your Roku.\n2. Click on the Notification Center in the lower-right corner of your PC's taskbar.\n3. Click on \"Project\" or \"Connect to a wireless display.\"\n4. Choose your Roku device once it appears in the list of devices.\n5. Open a web browser on your PC, and it will be mirrored on your Roku.\n\n### 2. Screencasting from an iOS Device:\nRoku also supports Apple AirPlay, which allows you to cast content from an iOS device to your Roku.\n\n#### Setup for iOS:\n1. Make sure your iOS device is connected to the same Wi-Fi network as your Roku.\n2. Ensure that AirPlay is enabled on your Roku by going to Settings > Apple AirPlay and HomeKit.\n3. Swipe down from the upper-right corner of your iOS device's screen to open the Control Center.\n4. Tap on \"Screen Mirroring\" and select your Roku device from the list.\n5. Open a web browser on your iOS device, and it should display on your Roku.\n\nKeep in mind that these methods depend on your devices being compatible and correctly set up. You may need to verify that your Roku model supports these features since older models may not offer screen mirroring or AirPlay support.",
